HEADWORD: Patefaction
<hw>Pat`e*fac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>patefactio</ets>, fr. <ets>patefacere</ets> to open;
<ets>patere</ets> to lie open + <ets>facere</ets> to make.]</ety>
<def>The act of opening, disclosing, or manifesting; open
declaration.</def> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

